img_path = "/home/robotics/content-classification/content_transfer"
img_names = ['horror_test', 'animation_test']

images = []

for name in img_names:
    img = cv2.imread(os.path.join(img_path, name), 1)
    img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    img = cv2.resize(img, (200, 150))
    img = np.array(img) / 255.0
    images.append(img)
    
images = np.array(images)

Visualize results¶

In [9]:
def show_image_and_label(X, y, classes, pred):
    """
    """
    background = dict(facecolor='white', alpha=0.8)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6), dpi=120)
    plt.imshow(X)
    plt.text(20, 50, 'label: ' + classes[y], bbox=background,
             fontsize='xx-large', color='blue')
    
    plt.text(20, 120, 'Prediction: ' + classes[pred], bbox=background,
            fontsize='xx-large', color='red')
    
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()
